#### Manual Verification:
- [ ] Search returns podcast results with id, title, coverImageUrl, authorName
- [ ] Subscriptions returns followed podcasts
- [ ] Cache files created in `CACHE_DIR/podcast_cache/`### Slice 4: RSS Generation

**Files**: `podimo/rss.go`, `main.go`

#### Automated Verification:
- [ ] `PodcastsToRss` produces valid RSS XML bytes
- [ ] `PodcastsToRss` sets channel title, description, link, language, author
- [ ] `PodcastsToRss` adds `itunes:image` at channel level when cover image exists
- [ ] `PodcastsToRss` sets `itunes:block=yes` when `publicFeeds=false`
- [ ] `buildFeedItem` creates item with title, description, enclosure, duration, pubDate
- [ ] `buildFeedItem` calls `URLHeadInfo` for content-length and content-type
- [ ] `ExtractAudioURL` returns audio URL and duration from `audio` field
- [ ] `ExtractAudioURL` falls back to `streamMedia` and rewrites HLS→MP3
- [ ] `URLHeadInfo` returns cached values on second call with same ID
- [ ] `URLHeadInfo` makes HEAD request with 3 retries and 1s backoff
- [ ] `URLHeadInfo` stores result in head cache after successful request
- [ ] `chunks` splits slice into chunks of correct size
- [ ] `GET /feed/{id}.xml` with valid auth returns `text/xml` with RSS content
- [ ] `GET /feed/{id}.xml` with invalid podcast ID returns 400
- [ ] `GET /feed/{id}.xml` for blocked podcast returns 410
- [ ] `GET /feed/{id}.xml` for non-existent podcast returns 404
- [ ] `GET /feed/{id}.xml` with invalid auth returns 401
- [ ] `GET /feed/{username}/{password}/{id}.xml` works with path credentials
- [ ] RSS passes [Cast Feed Validator](https://castfeedvalidator.com/) or similar

#### Manual Verification:
- [ ] Feed XML contains `<enclosure>` with url/length/type for each episode
- [ ] Feed XML contains `<itunes:duration>` for each episode
- [ ] Feed XML contains `<itunes:image>` at channel level
- [ ] Feed XML contains `<itunes:author>`
- [ ] Episode count matches expected podcast episode count
- [ ] HEAD cache files created in `CACHE_DIR/head_cache/`## Desired End State

### Usage

```bash
# Build single binary
go build -o podimo-rss .

# Run with .env
./podimo-rss

# Or with env vars
PODIMO_HOSTNAME=localhost:12104 ./podimo-rss
```

### RSS Feed Request

```bash
curl -u "user@example.com,nl,nl-NL:password" \
  http://localhost:12104/feed/12345678-1234-1234-1234-123456789abc.xml
```

### Health Check

```bash
curl http://localhost:12104/health
# → {"status":"ok","service":"podimo-rss"}
```

## File Map

- `go.mod`               # NEW — Go module definition with minimal deps
- `config.go`            # NEW — Configuration loading, block list, constants
- `main.go`              # NEW — HTTP server, routes, middleware, templates
- `templates/index.html`   # NEW — Search/form template (embedded)
- `templates/feed_location.html` # NEW — Feed URL display template (embedded)
- `podimo/cache.go`      # NEW — File-based JSON cache with TTL
- `podimo/graphql.go`    # NEW — Thin GraphQL HTTP wrapper
- `podimo/client.go`     # NEW — PodimoClient, auth, podcast fetching
- `podimo/rss.go`        # NEW — RSS generation with eduncan911/podcast

## Ordering Constraints

1. Slice 1 (Foundation) must complete before any other slice.
2. Slice 2 (GraphQL + Auth + Cache) depends on Slice 1 for config and logging.
3. Slice 3 (Podcast Operations) depends on Slice 2 for GraphQL client and auth.
4. Slice 4 (RSS Generation) depends on Slice 3 for podcast data and Slice 2 for HEAD cache.

No parallel slices — each builds on the previous.

## Verification Notes

- Run `go test ./...` — all tests pass
- Run `go vet ./...` — no warnings
- Run `gofmt -d .` — no formatting issues
- Test `/health` returns `{"status":"ok"}`
- Test `/` renders form with regions and locales
- Test `/search?q=test` with valid credentials returns JSON results
- Test `/subscriptions` with valid credentials returns JSON results
- Test `/feed/{id}.xml` with valid credentials returns valid RSS XML
- Test invalid podcast ID returns 400
- Test blocked podcast returns 410
- Test non-existent podcast returns 404
- Test invalid credentials return 401 with `WWW-Authenticate` header
- Test rate limiting blocks after 8 requests in 10 seconds
- Verify RSS passes [Cast Feed Validator](https://castfeedvalidator.com/) or similar
- Verify `itunes:image` appears at channel and item level
- Verify `enclosure` has correct url/length/type
- Verify cache files are created in `CACHE_DIR`
- Verify cache TTL eviction works (wait or modify file timestamps)

## Performance Considerations

- Go's goroutines replace Python's `asyncio.gather` for concurrent episode HEAD requests (chunks of 5).
- No GIL means true parallelism for concurrent feed requests.
- Serial pagination for GraphQL episodes remains the same (100 per request, offset loop).
- File-based cache JSON serialization is slower than SQLite but negligible for this workload (<1000 entries, low write rate).
- Single binary startup is near-instant compared to Python interpreter + dependency loading.

## Migration Notes

This is a greenfield rewrite, not an in-place migration. The Python codebase remains intact. Deployment switches from `python main.py` to `./podimo-rss`. Environment variables and `.env` files are compatible. Cache directory structure changes from SQLite files to JSON files — old caches are ignored and rebuilt.

Rollback strategy: Stop the Go binary, restart the Python service. Both can coexist on different ports for A/B testing.

